========,1,preface.
Worthington Township is a township in Nobles County, Minnesota, United States.
The population was 316 at the 2000 census.
========,2,Geography.
According to the United States Census Bureau, the township has a total area of 28.6 square miles (74.1 km²), all land.
The main geographic feature in Worthington Township is Lake Okabena.
Okabena means "home of the heron" is the Sioux language.
